HEADWORD: Stewardly
<hw>Stew"ard*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a manner, or with the
care, of a steward.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To be <qex>stewardly</qex> dispensed, not wastefully spent.</q>
